chore(ci): align repo with backend-ci + lint gates; add deploy-dev workflow

Bring all files into line with the formatters CI runs on every push so the
`dev` branch merge is clean:

- prettier (`pnpm format:check`): 56 files reformatted across frontend,
  vscode-extension, website, mobile-app, infra YAML, workflow YAML, root
  config files. Whitespace / quote-style only — no behavior change.
- ruff format (`uv run ruff format --check app tests`): 334 files already
  formatted; the duplicate docstring in app/agents/devops/nodes/__init__.py
  was removed (it was causing E402 against all sibling imports), and the
  long commit_message f-string in configure_cicd.py was wrapped.
- ruff check (`uv run ruff check app tests`): import sort + 10 auto-fixes
  applied (unused imports, import-block ordering, redundant string-typed
  annotation).
- mypy (`uv run mypy app`): 21 pre-existing DevOps agent typing errors fixed
  with annotation-only changes (no runtime behavior change). Pytest still
  442 passed / 2 skipped, identical to the pre-edit baseline.
  - agent.py: typed `__init__` args as `Any` (kwargs delegated to BaseAgent);
    cast `self.graph` to Any inside execute so mypy stops complaining about
    `.ainvoke` on the LangGraph CompiledGraph.
  - graph.py: inner join nodes typed as `dict[str, Any]`; `build_devops_graph`
    return type is now `Any`; `graph` local cast to Any to bypass LangGraph's
    Pydantic-state NodeInputT=Never inference. `checkpointer` parameter
    typed as `Any | None` to match BaseAgent.
  - run_local.py: cast compiled graph to Any for `.ainvoke`.
  - tools.py: `update_file(..., sha or "")` to satisfy PyGithub's `str` arg;
    `_TOOL_DISPATCH` typed as `dict[str, Callable[..., Awaitable[...]]]`;
    added `Awaitable, Callable` imports.
  - tests/integration/test_agent_run.py: None-guard for `vpc_config.vpc_id`
    before `.startswith` (no behavior change; the assertion already implied
    non-None).

Also wires the dev-branch deploy pipeline:

- .github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml: new workflow for `push: [dev]` and
  `workflow_dispatch`. Matches the manual ECS setup — single
  `autofounderai-cluster`, per-env service `autofounderai-backend-dev`.
- .github/workflows/deploy-staging.yml: renamed cluster/service to
  `autofounderai-cluster` / `autofounderai-backend-uat`.
- .github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml: renamed cluster/service to
  `autofounderai-cluster` / `autofounderai-backend-prod`.

Backend Dockerfile:

- Install terraform 1.9.8 in the runtime stage so the DevOps agent's
  `terraform_plan_module` tool works inside the ECS container (Path A:
  `terraform init -backend=false` + `terraform validate -json`, no AWS
  credentials required).
- Set `TF_PLUGIN_CACHE_DIR=/home/appuser/.terraform.d/plugin-cache` to
  share provider downloads across module inits in the same task lifetime.

Validation:
- `uv run ruff check app tests` → All checks passed
- `uv run ruff format --check app tests` → 334 files already formatted
- `uv run mypy app` → Success: no issues found in 239 source files
- `uv run pytest` (fast suite) → 442 passed, 2 skipped in 43.37s
- `pnpm format:check` → All matched files use Prettier code style
